{"author":"Claude","data":{"alias":"gnu-whale-ichor","description":"# P2.2 ‚Äî Authenticated identity (in-event) + optional detached signature\n\n## Context (problem + research)\n\n`COMMENT.author`, `CREATE.assignee`, and `claim --assignee` are unauthenticated\nfree strings; anyone with push access to `origin/tickets` can forge any author and\nreplay trusts the bytes. For a store whose value is multi-writer coordination +\naudit trail, \"who did this\" has no trustworthy answer. **git-bug** records author\nas a reference to a versioned identity, signing is **optional** and **detached**\n(OpenPGP over the commit), verified against keys the identity declared valid **at\nthat Lamport time** (`ValidKeysAtTime`, `entity/dag/operation_pack.go`). Per-commit\nsigning alone cannot attest per-event authorship in rebar because commit<->event is\nmany-to-one (compaction folds N events into 1 commit; the reconciler batches), so\n**in-event** identity must be primary. The sigstore/OCI lesson: sign the literal\nbytes ‚Äî safe here because P1.0 makes canonical bytes single-impl.\n\n## Evidence (experiments)\n\n- EXP-gpg: ed25519 detached sign/verify/tamper round-trip over canonical bytes works.\n- EXP3: `ssh-keygen` may be ABSENT; signing must be opt-in with graceful fallback.\n- EXP-R8 (real code): the host already **force-signs commits** (`commit.gpgsign=true`,\n  ssh); rebar's `--no-verify` does not bypass `-S`. Writes still succeeded (env's\n  signing server), so ambient signing is a latent portability note.\n\n## What / Implementation detail\n\n1. **Primary ‚Äî recorded identity.** Resolve author from `git config\n   user.email`/`user.name` at write time, stamp the event `author`. Optionally store\n   a **detached signature over `canonical_bytes(event without \"sig\")`** (covers\n   author/timestamp/uuid/data) in an additive optional field ‚Äî independent of git\n   commits, preserved through reconciler batching.\n2. **Compaction caveat.** A SNAPSHOT stores only `source_event_uuids`\n   (`ticket-compact.sh:263`), not per-event identity. Extend the SNAPSHOT payload to\n   carry each folded event's recorded identity/signature, and `process_snapshot`\n   (`reducer/_processors.py:337-341`) to surface it, so verification reads back\n   through `*.retired` folds.\n3. **Secondary ‚Äî optional commit signing** (`identity.sign`/`REBAR_SIGN`): also\n   `git commit -S` on the single-event Python/STATUS paths. Because ambient signing\n   already happens (EXP-R8), pin `-c commit.gpgsign=false` on internal commits unless\n   `REBAR_SIGN` is set, so a misconfigured host signer can't fail a write.\n4. **Verification advisory:** `show`/`fsck` surface `identity:\n   verified|unverified|unsigned`; replay NEVER rejects (one bad push must not wedge\n   a store; cross-clone rejection is unenforceable).\n\n## Limitation (state it)\n\nFlat in-event identity cannot express key rotation (git-bug's `ValidKeysAtTime`).\nDocument it; note the forward-compat path (versioned identity entities with\nHLC-stamped key sets) so it can be retrofitted ‚Äî git-bug needed a migration tool\nto add this later.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Sign a write -> `fsck` reports `verified`; tamper an author -> `unverified` (not\n  silently trusted); a folded (compacted) signed event still verifies through the\n  SNAPSHOT; zero-config path -> `unsigned`, no errors.\n- Default install experience unchanged; signing fully opt-in.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] resolve + stamp in-event author identity on every write\n- [ ] optional detached signature over `canonical_bytes(event without sig)` (depends on P1.0)\n- [ ] SNAPSHOT payload + `process_snapshot` carry/surface folded-event identity\n- [ ] optional `git commit -S` secondary; pin `commit.gpgsign=false` unless REBAR_SIGN\n- [ ] advisory verification in show/fsck; replay never rejects; key-rotation limit documented\n\nSee `docs/remediation-implementation-plan.md` (P2.2).\n","id":"e68d-b701-4dd9-47aa","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":["oss-remediation","phase-2"],"ticket_type":"epic","title":"P2.2 ‚Äî Authenticated identity (in-event) + optional detached signature"},"env_id":"40ed2498-b23e-4d88-96df-b27ef70d5016","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1781386748931312299,"uuid":"348f395d-7270-46ea-8fd8-815d5b7264c8"}